description: A slot1EncoderLossOfVideoInputActive trap signifies that
there is loss of video input on slot1Encoder.
This trap message is available only if
vbrickBoxUserInformationPartNumber is xxxx-xxxx-xxx1.

event.Summary: Loss of video input on slot1 encoder

description: A slot1EncoderLossOfVideoInputCleared trap signifies that
the loss of video input on slot1Encoder is recovered.
This trap message is available only if
vbrickBoxUserInformationPartNumber is xxxx-xxxx-xxx1.

event.Summary: Loss of video input recovered on slot1 encoder

description: A slot2EncoderLossOfVideoInputActive trap signifies that

event.Summary: Loss of video input recovered on slot2 encoder

description: A hardDiskFull trap signifies that all the available
free space on the hard disk has been exhausted. Attempts to
store new information to the disk will fail. This trap is
emitted whenever available space falls below 100 MBytes.
The recorder automatically stops after this trap is sent.

event.Summary: Hard disk is full
